# Frontend Governance (Autoconnecto)

Autoconnecto frontend is a Vite + React + TypeScript app with:
- A large registry-driven dashboard widget system (`frontend/src/features/dashboards/registry/widgetRegistry.ts`)
- Realtime consumption over Socket.IO (backend path `/socket.io`)
- Telemetry stream normalization/buffering (`frontend/src/realtime/telemetry.store.ts`)
- Attribute update merging in dashboard context (`frontend/src/features/dashboards/context/DashboardContext.tsx`)

## Deterministic realtime rules

- **One socket client ownership model**:
  - exactly one module/provider creates the Socket.IO client instance
  - listeners must be registered via a controlled API to prevent duplicate listeners
  - subscriptions (`subscribe_device` / `unsubscribe_device`) must be ref-counted or lifecycle-bound
- Do not introduce new ad-hoc sockets in feature modules.

## Widget system anti-drift rules

- Widget `type` strings are stable API. Renames are breaking changes unless dual-supported.
- Any new widget must include:
  - registry entry (or auto-discovery export) with stable `type`
  - config UI (if configurable) with deterministic defaults
  - explicit data source expectations (telemetry/alarm/device)
- Avoid hidden dependencies on `localStorage` keys unless documented and namespaced.

## Telemetry/attribute event rules

- Payload normalization belongs in shared utilities/stores, not in each widget.
- Attribute updates are partial and must be merged; do not overwrite whole device state on partial updates.

## Deployment safety (frontend)

- Frontend env (`VITE_*`) values must be documented when changed (URLs, websocket base).
- Avoid hardcoding backend URLs; use env + central API client modules.

